                                                                                                               Tax refund for MTNL 
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, March 27: State-owned Mahanagar Telephone Nigam Limited (MTNL) today said it had received tax refunds worth Rs 516.18 crore for 2001-02 and 2003-04.        
	The company also received an interest of Rs 131.47 crore, which will increase its profit for financial year 2008-09.        
	For the quarter ended December 2008, the company reported a net profit of Rs 58.27 crore compared with Rs 94.18 crore in the year-ago period.        
	Total income increased to Rs 1,404.4 crore in the December quarter from Rs 1,322.4 crore a year ago.         
	It is gearing up for the launch of 3G in Mumbai in May after the February rollout in Delhi.        
	With mobile penetration in both Delhi and Mumbai  MTNLs area of operations nearing 100 per cent, the firm is looking to tap new segments of users to spur revenues.                                                                                                                                        
